---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About Grownetics | Built by People Who've Been in the Grow Rooms"
  description="Grownetics builds the complete CEA technology stack: monitoring, automation, facility design, and consulting. 60+ years combined experience. 1M+ sq ft deployed. Boulder, CO."
  canonical="/about"
>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[55vh] flex items-center graph-grid pt-16" aria-labelledby="about-headline">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
      <img
        src="/images/bg-about.png"
        alt=""
        role="presentation"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-15"
        loading="eager"
        width="1200"
        height="800"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--bg) 60%, transparent)"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="container relative z-10 py-20">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <div class="section-ref mb-6">
          <div class="section-ref-bar"></div>
          <span class="ref-label">§ 001 · Who We Are</span>
        </div>

        <h1 id="about-headline" class="display-xl mb-5">
          Built by people who've been<br />
          <span style="color: var(--green)">in the grow rooms.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl font-display italic text-ink-2 mb-4">
          Grownetics was founded on a simple frustration: the technology available to
          commercial CEA operators was too fragile, too fragmented, and too far removed
          from how cultivation actually works.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-ink-3 leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
          We didn't build our products from a software background. We built them from grow
          room experience: from watching good growers fight bad systems, from watching
          efficient facilities get squeezed by rising input costs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       § 001 - BY THE NUMBERS
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section-surface">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="section-ref">
        <div class="section-ref-bar"></div>
        <span class="ref-label">§ 001 · By the Numbers</span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 reveal">
        {[
          { value: "1M+", label: "sq ft managed", detail: "CO · CA · Canada · International" },
          { value: "60+", label: "Years combined experience", detail: "Engineering + cultivation expertise" },
          { value: "UL", label: "Certified controls", detail: "Industrial-grade reliability" },
          { value: "UC", label: "Research affiliated", detail: "University of Colorado studies" },
        ].map((stat) => (
          <div class="card p-5 text-center">
            <div class="stat-number text-2xl mb-1">{stat.value}</div>
            <div class="font-display font-semibold text-sm text-ink mb-1">{stat.label}</div>
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-3 leading-snug">{stat.detail}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       § 002 - ORIGIN STORY
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="section-ref">
        <div class="section-ref-bar"></div>
        <span class="ref-label">§ 002 · Origin</span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="reveal">
          <h2 class="display-md mb-6">
            We didn't build from<br />a software background.<br />
            <span style="color: var(--terracotta)">We built from grow room experience.</span>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-ink-3 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            From watching good growers fight bad systems. From watching efficient facilities
            get squeezed by rising input costs. From seeing what happens when a cultivation
            operation doesn't have the tools it actually needs.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-3 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            That frustration turned into CropVision. Then Unity. Then Foundation.
            And soon, Grownetics OS. Everything we build is for the operator who takes
            their craft seriously and needs technology that takes it seriously too.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-3 leading-relaxed">
            A decade later, we're still building the same way: in the grow room,
            not the conference room. Our technology is built by people who've debugged
            climate drift at 2am and redesigned facility layouts to fix airflow problems
            that didn't show up on any blueprint.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { year: "2015", event: "Founded in Boulder, CO" },
            { year: "2016", event: "First commercial deployment in Colorado" },
            { year: "2018", event: "Expanded to California and Canada" },
            { year: "2020", event: "1M+ sq ft milestone crossed" },
            { year: "2022", event: "UL Certification achieved for Unity" },
            { year: "2025", event: "Grownetics OS development begins" },
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="card p-4">
              <div class="font-mono text-xs text-gold tracking-widest mb-1">{item.year}</div>
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">{item.event}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       § 003 - WHAT WE BELIEVE
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="section-ref">
        <div class="section-ref-bar" style="background: var(--green)"></div>
        <span class="ref-label">§ 003 · What Drives Us</span>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-xl mb-12">
        <h2 class="display-lg mb-4">
          We believe the best technology<br />is invisible.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-ink-3 leading-relaxed">
          The best facility technology does its job so well that operators stop thinking
          about it and start thinking about cultivation. That's the standard we hold
          ourselves to: not "feature-rich" but "friction-free." Not "powerful" but "reliable."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5 reveal">
        {[
          {
            principle: "The grower isn't broken. The system is.",
            detail: "Yield variation is almost always a systems problem: environmental, equipment, or protocol. Not genetics. Not the grower.",
          },
          {
            principle: "Evidence first. Philosophy second.",
            detail: "We lead with specs, data, and concrete claims, not narratives about what cannabis cultivation should be.",
          },
          {
            principle: "Vendor lock-in is a design choice, not a requirement.",
            detail: "Open sensor ecosystems, exportable data, and transparent pricing aren't optional. They're how we'd want to buy technology.",
          },
          {
            principle: "Precision at scale isn't a feature. It's survival.",
            detail: "As CEA markets mature, the gap between efficient and inefficient operations determines who's operating in five years.",
          },
          {
            principle: "Technology amplifies expertise. It doesn't replace it.",
            detail: "CropVision and Unity make good growers better. They don't turn untrained staff into cultivators.",
          },
          {
            principle: "If we can't explain the ROI, we don't deserve the sale.",
            detail: "Every Grownetics engagement starts with a clear statement of what it costs, what it returns, and how you'll know it worked.",
          },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="card p-6">
            <div class="w-6 h-0.5 mb-4" style="background: var(--green)"></div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-ink mb-2 leading-snug">{item.principle}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-3 leading-relaxed">{item.detail}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       § 004 - TEAM CREDENTIALS
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section-surface">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="section-ref">
        <div class="section-ref-bar" style="background: var(--gold)"></div>
        <span class="ref-label">§ 004 · The Team</span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div class="reveal">
          <h2 class="display-md mb-6">
            60+ years of combined experience<br />in the rooms that matter.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-ink-3 leading-relaxed mb-5">
            The Grownetics team is a mix of licensed master growers, controls engineers,
            facility designers, compliance specialists, and systems architects.
            Not one or the other. All of the above.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-3 leading-relaxed mb-5">
            Our controls engineers hold UL certifications and have designed panels for
            commercial agricultural, pharmaceutical, and industrial applications.
            Our cultivation consultants have run head grower and director roles
            across CO, CA, and Canadian markets.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-3 leading-relaxed">
            Combined, the team has deployed, operated, and optimized over 1 million
            square feet of commercial cultivation space, in climates ranging from
            Colorado's altitude to British Columbia's humidity.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal space-y-3">
          {[
            { area: "Controls Engineering", detail: "UL 508A panels, predictive algorithms, industrial automation" },
            { area: "Cultivation Science", detail: "Licensed master growers, tissue culture to harvest, Total Crop Steering™" },
            { area: "Facility Design", detail: "Greenfield + retrofit, CAD/BIM, compliance documentation" },
            { area: "Systems Architecture", detail: "IoT networks, sensor integration, data infrastructure" },
            { area: "Regulatory Compliance", detail: "CO, CA, Canada: licensing, track & trace, audits" },
            { area: "Research Partnerships", detail: "University of Colorado affiliated studies and data validation" },
          ].map((e) => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 rounded" style="background: var(--surface-2); border: 1px solid var(--border-light)">
              <div class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-green flex-shrink-0 mt-2"></div>
              <div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-sm text-ink">{e.area}</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-ink-3 mt-0.5">{e.detail}</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       § 005 - CLIENTS
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="section-ref">
        <div class="section-ref-bar"></div>
        <span class="ref-label">§ 005 · Deployed In</span>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
        <h2 class="display-md mb-4">Real facilities. Real results.</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-3 leading-relaxed">
          From boutique craft cultivators to multi-site operations, our clients
          share one thing: they take yield seriously.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-5 reveal">
        {[
          {
            name: "The Work",
            location: "Colorado",
            detail: "Full CropVision + Unity deployment. 18% yield increase in first cycle.",
          },
          {
            name: "House of Cultivars",
            location: "Colorado",
            detail: "Monitoring and cultivation consulting. Consistent 3.0+ lbs per light.",
          },
          {
            name: "Green Horizons",
            location: "California",
            detail: "Facility design + Unity. Caught three critical airflow issues pre-build.",
          },
          {
            name: "Fields of Light",
            location: "Canada",
            detail: "Full stack deployment. International market expertise applied.",
          },
        ].map((client) => (
          <div class="card p-5">
            <div class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-1">{client.name}</div>
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-gold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">{client.location}</div>
            <p class="text-xs text-ink-3 leading-relaxed">{client.detail}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <CTASection
    sectionRef="006"
    eyebrow="Work With Us"
    headline="Want to know if we're the right fit? Let's find out together."
    body="Discovery calls are one hour, completely free, and genuinely useful whether you work with us or not. Come with your hardest constraint. We'll come with honest answers."
    cta={{ label: "Book a Discovery Call →", href: "/contact" }}
    ctaSecondary={{ label: "Email hello@grownetics.com", href: "mailto:hello@grownetics.com" }}
    variant="dark"
  />

</Base>
